cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI 

This paper deals with the problem of printed text recognition from images, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper proposes a mathematical model for the procedural construction of printed text, which involves the use of deep learning methods (cs.LG) and multi-task learning (cs.AI). The model also addresses the problem of missing characters in incomplete text regions, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
